---
import BaseLayout from "../layout/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "@ui/Button.astro";

const pageTitle = "How it Works";
const pageDescription =
  "A simple, collaborative workflow for assisted nurse scheduling at Critical Access Hospitals in Texas. Your rules, your final approval, fewer headaches.";

const ctaLink = "https://cal.com/gautham-8bdvdx/30min";
---

<BaseLayout
  seo={{
    title: pageTitle,
    description: pageDescription,
  }}
>
  {/* Dark hero */}
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-slate-950 -mt-32 sm:-mt-36 lg:-mt-40">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -top-40 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 h-[400px] w-[600px] rounded-full bg-teal-700/20 blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 pt-44 pb-16 sm:px-6 sm:pt-48 lg:px-8 lg:pt-52">
      <div class="mb-5 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-teal-700/40 bg-teal-900/40 px-4 py-1.5">
        <span class="h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-teal-400"></span>
        <span class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest text-teal-300 uppercase">Clear workflow. Predictable handoffs.</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-balance text-4xl font-black text-white sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
        {pageTitle}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
        Assisted scheduling that fits into your current process. You keep control and final approval. We reduce the weekly load.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
        <Button href="/pilot" variant="primary">
          View the Pilot
        </Button>
        <a
          href={ctaLink}
          class="rounded-lg px-6 py-2.5 text-center font-medium transition-colors duration-300 border-2 border-slate-600 text-slate-300 hover:border-teal-600 hover:text-white"
        >
          Ask a question
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* What you send / What you get */}
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
      <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-teal-600">Simple handoff</p>
          <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
            What you send us. What you get back.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-slate-600">
            We work with the format you already use. Excel is fine. No new software for your staff.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-7">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900">What you send us</h3>
            <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1.5 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-teal-600"></span>
                <span class="text-slate-700">Staff roster via Excel (roles, competency levels, home units)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1.5 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-teal-600"></span>
                <span class="text-slate-700">PRN availability submissions and leave requests</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1.5 size-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-teal-600"></span>
                <span class="text-slate-700">Unit rules: weekend requirements, escalation order, OT thresholds</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600">Export your current data, edit in Excel, re-import. Simple.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-teal-700 bg-teal-50/50 p-7">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900">What you get back</h3>
            <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-teal-700">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span class="text-slate-700">Compliant, post-ready schedule (21 rules checked automatically)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-teal-700">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span class="text-slate-700">Multiple variants to compare (coverage vs cost vs fairness)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-teal-700">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span class="text-slate-700">Auto-recommended replacements when leave is approved</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-teal-700">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span class="text-slate-700">Full audit trail of every change for compliance</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">Nothing is final until your team signs off.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-6">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900">Delivered every Thursday, 3pm</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">PDF schedule, Excel workbook, and a manager summary with flagged items. Ready for your review before posting.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* 4-step workflow */}
  <section class="bg-slate-50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-teal-600">The process</p>
        <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
          Four steps. No surprises.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-slate-600">A structured collaboration that respects your existing process.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto mt-14 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700">Step 1</p>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Kickoff and rules</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">We document your rules, constraints, and what a good schedule looks like for your unit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700">Step 2</p>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Inputs and handoff</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">Your team shares availability and coverage requirements in the format you already use.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700">Step 3</p>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Build and validate</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">We build the schedule and check all 21 rules: coverage, compliance, fairness, and conflict gaps.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-teal-700 bg-teal-50/50 p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-700">Step 4</p>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">Your review and approval</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">Your team reviews, adjusts if needed, and approves. You stay in full control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* 13 + 8 Rules Detail */}
  <section class="bg-slate-950">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-teal-400">Built-in compliance</p>
        <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
          21 rules validated on every schedule
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-400">
          Every draft is automatically checked before it reaches you. No rule can be quietly skipped.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-14 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">

        {/* 13 Compliance and Safety Rules */}
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900 p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <span class="flex size-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-red-500/20 border border-red-500/30">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-red-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
              </svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-red-400">Required</p>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">13 Compliance and Safety Rules</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-6">These must pass on every schedule. If any fail, the draft is flagged before delivery.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              "Charge nurse on every shift",
              "Minimum RN-to-patient ratio met per shift",
              "Minimum 2 rest days per 7-day period per nurse",
              "Minimum rest between shifts: 11 hours standard, 12 hours after a night shift",
              "No double-booking: a nurse cannot be assigned to overlapping shifts",
              "No scheduling during approved PTO",
              "PRN staff within contracted availability",
              "Required certifications present per shift (BLS, ACLS)",
              "Float staff within licensed scope of practice",
              "OT threshold not exceeded without flag",
              "Minimum total staff count per shift",
              "Skill mix requirement satisfied per unit",
              "All schedule changes are documented with the approver detail",
            ].map((rule) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 flex size-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-red-500/20 border border-red-500/40">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-3 w-3 text-red-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span class="text-sm text-slate-300">{rule}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        {/* 8 Fairness Goals */}
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900 p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <span class="flex size-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-teal-500/20 border border-teal-500/30">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-teal-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.519 4.674a1 1 0 00.95.69h4.915c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-3.976 2.888a1 1 0 00-.363 1.118l1.518 4.674c.3.922-.755 1.688-1.538 1.118l-3.976-2.888a1 1 0 00-1.176 0l-3.976 2.888c-.783.57-1.838-.197-1.538-1.118l1.518-4.674a1 1 0 00-.363-1.118l-3.976-2.888c-.784-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h4.914a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.519-4.674z" />
              </svg>
            </span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-teal-400">Optimized</p>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">8 Fairness and Preference Goals</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mb-6">These are actively optimized on every draft. Flags are surfaced so you can choose the best trade-off.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              "Weekend equity: no nurse should work more than 3 weekends in any 6-week period",
              "Holiday shifts distributed fairly across the team, tracked annually",
              "Charge duty distributed evenly across eligible staff",
              "Night shift burden shared across the team",
              "Staff shift preferences honored when possible",
              "Overtime spread evenly when OT is unavoidable",
              "Extra hours above FTE minimized per nurse",
              "Float pool assignments rotated fairly",
            ].map((goal) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 flex size-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-500/20 border border-teal-500/40">
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-3 w-3 text-teal-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span class="text-sm text-slate-300">{goal}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl border border-teal-700/40 bg-teal-900/20 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-teal-300">Every fairness flag is explained. You see which trade-off was made and why, so you can approve or adjust with full context.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* FAQ */}
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-teal-600">Common questions</p>
          <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
            Questions about the process
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-12 divide-y divide-slate-200">
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-semibold text-slate-900">
              <span>How do we get our data in?</span>
              <span class="ml-4 shrink-0 text-teal-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">Excel upload. Export your current data, edit, re-import anytime. No new software for your staff.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-semibold text-slate-900">
              <span>What happens when someone calls out?</span>
              <span class="ml-4 shrink-0 text-teal-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">The system auto-finds the top 3 replacement candidates with reasons. You approve with one click. You do not have to call us, but we are reachable if something unusual comes up.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-semibold text-slate-900">
              <span>How is fairness tracked?</span>
              <span class="ml-4 shrink-0 text-teal-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">Weekends (no more than 3 per 6-week period), holidays (tracked annually), overtime, and charge duty distribution. All automatic.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-semibold text-slate-900">
              <span>What about compliance and audits?</span>
              <span class="ml-4 shrink-0 text-teal-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">Full audit trail of every change: who, what, when. Exportable anytime. Staffing committee packet ready in one click.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-semibold text-slate-900">
              <span>What if we already use a scheduling system?</span>
              <span class="ml-4 shrink-0 text-teal-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">We do not replace your EMR. Most pilots come from teams using spreadsheets or a basic tool that does not enforce rules. We deliver the schedule so you do not have to build it.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* CTA */}
  <section class="bg-slate-950">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[85rem] px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-28">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-teal-400">3 spots open</p>
        <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
          Ready to test this in your hospital?
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-slate-400">
          The pilot is a low-risk way to see if assisted scheduling reduces effort and stress for your team. Free for 60 days.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center">
          <Button href="/pilot" variant="primary">
            View the Pilot
          </Button>
          <a
            href={ctaLink}
            class="rounded-lg px-6 py-2.5 text-center font-medium transition-colors duration-300 border-2 border-slate-600 text-slate-300 hover:border-teal-600 hover:text-white"
          >
            Book a call
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
